{"word":"ἀρχηγός","slug":"ἀρχηγός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀρχηγός, οῦ, ὁ</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀρχή\">ἀρχή</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἄγω\">ἄγω</a></el>; the noun is more <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ freq.\">freq.</a> than the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adj.\">adj.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀρχηγός\">ἀρχηγός</a>, όν</el>]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘one who enjoys a preeminent position’, <b><i>leader, ruler</i> <a href='B:510 5:31'>Ac 5:31</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘one noted for beginning something’, <b><i>originator, founder</i> <a href='B:510 3:15'>Ac 3:15</a></b> (some would place this in 1)<b>; <a href='B:650 2:10'>Hb 2:10</a>; <a href='B:650 12:2'>12:2</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀρχή\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀρχιερατικός\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}